== Using syncExec() and asyncExec()
	
		In Eclipse 3.x API based plug-ins you cannot use dependency injection
		to get the
		`UISynchronize`
		instance injected.
	
	
		In this case you can use the
		`Display`
		class which provides the 
		`syncExec()`
		and
		`asyncExec()`
		methods to update the user interface from another
		thread.
	

	
